  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 200°C (400°F).",
    "Toss the chickpeas with olive oil, smoked paprika, cumin, cayenne, salt, and pepper until evenly coated.",
    "Spread the chickpeas on a baking sheet and roast for 25 minutes, turning once, until golden and crispy.",
    "While the chickpeas roast, whisk together tahini, lemon juice, garlic, water, and salt until smooth and silky.",
    "Prepare the quinoa according to package instructions.",
    "In a bowl, combine the cooked quinoa, roasted chickpeas, and chopped cilantro.",
    "Drizzle the tahini sauce over the bowl and toss gently to coat.",
    "Squeeze a lemon wedge over the top for brightness.",
    "Serve immediately, optionally adding extra cilantro or a pinch of smoked paprika."
  ],
